---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contact - Leszek Pomianowski">
  <div class="page">
    <h1>Contact</h1>
    <p>
      I'm always interested in connecting with fellow developers, discussing collaboration opportunities, 
      or helping with projects that align with my expertise in .NET development and modern UI frameworks.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
    <p>
      Whether you're looking for technical expertise, open-source collaboration, professional consulting, 
      or just want to discuss ideas about modern Windows development, I'd love to hear from you.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Email</h3>
    <p>
      For business inquiries, collaboration proposals, or technical discussions, you can reach me at:
      <br><strong>support at lepo.co</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      Please replace "at" with @ when sending your email. I typically respond within 24-48 hours during business days.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Professional Services</h3>
    <p>
      For professional support, consulting, or custom development services, visit 
      <a href="https://lepo.co/support" target="_blank" rel="noopener">lepo.co/support</a> 
      to learn about available support plans and services.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Online Presence</h2>
    <p>You can also find me on various platforms:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub:</strong> 
        <a href="https://github.com/lepoco" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@lepoco</a> - 
        Primary development activity and open-source projects
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub Sponsors:</strong> 
        <a href="https://github.com/sponsors/lepoco" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Support my work</a> - 
        Support ongoing open-source development
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Professional Profile:</strong> 
        <a href="https://github.com/pomianowski" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@pomianowski</a> - 
        Professional GitHub profile
      </li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>What I'm Looking For</h2>
    <p>I'm particularly interested in collaborating on:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Open Source Projects</strong> - Especially those involving .NET, WPF, or developer tooling</li>
      <li><strong>Microsoft Ecosystem</strong> - Projects that integrate with or enhance Microsoft technologies</li>
      <li><strong>Developer Experience</strong> - Tools and frameworks that make developers more productive</li>
      <li><strong>Modern UI/UX</strong> - Bringing modern design principles to desktop applications</li>
      <li><strong>AI and Automation</strong> - Projects involving MCP servers or AI-powered development tools</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Response Times</h2>
    <p>
      I aim to respond to all inquiries promptly, though response times may vary based on the nature 
      of your request and current project commitments:
    </p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Business Inquiries:</strong> 24-48 hours</li>
      <li><strong>Technical Questions:</strong> 2-3 business days</li>
      <li><strong>Collaboration Proposals:</strong> 3-5 business days</li>
      <li><strong>Open Source Issues:</strong> Best effort basis via GitHub</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Before You Contact Me</h2>
    <p>To help me provide the best response, please consider including:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Project Context:</strong> Brief description of your project or idea</li>
      <li><strong>Collaboration Type:</strong> What kind of involvement you're looking for</li>
      <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> Any relevant deadlines or timeframes</li>
      <li><strong>Technical Details:</strong> Relevant technologies or platforms involved</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>
      For technical support related to my open-source projects, please first check the project's 
      GitHub repository for existing issues and documentation. For general questions about using 
      WPF UI or other libraries, the GitHub Discussions section is often the best place to start.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      Looking forward to connecting and potentially working together on interesting projects!
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .page ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }
  
  .page li {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }
  
  .page h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  .page h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
